'''David Messer''' is an [[Australia]]n [[List of cartoonists|cartoonist]].<ref>{{cite news |author=Luke Davies  |title=Herg√© and me |url=http://www.smh.com.au/entertainment/movies/herg-and-me-20111201-1o7jw.html |quote= |pages= |work=Sydney Morning Herald |location= |date=3 December 2011  |accessdate=2015-03-07 }}</ref> He is best known for his comic book adaptations of [[William Shakespeare|Shakespeare's]] ''Macbeth'' and ''The Tempest'', both published in Australia by [[Random House]] in late [[2005 in comics|2005]]. <ref>{{Citation | author1=Jensen, Michael P | title=Comic Book Shakespeare, Part II.(William Shakespeare)(Critical essay) | journal=Shakespeare Newsletter | publication-date=2007-03-22 | publisher=Shakespeare Newsletter | volume=57 | issue=1 | pages=2(6) | issn=0037-3214 }}</ref><ref>{{Citation | author1=Jensen, Michael P | title=Comic Book Shakespeare, Part III.(Critical essay) | journal=Shakespeare Newsletter | publication-date=2007-09-22 | publisher=Shakespeare Newsletter | volume=57 | issue=2 | pages=42(7) | issn=0037-3214 }}</ref> Each book features the full text, complete with footnotes, and close to 1,000 illustrated panels per book. He has produced a full-colour version of "Romeo and Juliet".

Other books he has illustrated include [[Malcolm Knox (author)|Malcolm Knox]]'s humorous history of Australia, ''Australia in 1788 Words or Less'', [[Paul Clitheroe|Paul Clitheroe's]] ''Make Your Fortune by 40'' and ''Why Should I?'' (a guide to the law for children). Messer has also contributed cartoons and illustrations to numerous newspapers and magazines, including the [[The Spectator|Spectator]] in the UK, and the [[The Sydney Morning Herald|Sydney Morning Herald]], the [[The Australian|Australian]], and the [[The Bulletin|Bulletin]] in Australia.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nma.gov.au/exhibitions/behind_the_lines/about_the_artists|title=About the artists {{!}} National Museum of Australia|website=www.nma.gov.au|access-date=2016-06-27}}</ref>

Messer has been reviewing books for the [[Sydney Morning Herald]] since at least 2006.<ref>{{cite news |author=David Messer  |title=Struck by Lightning |url=http://www.smh.com.au/news/book-reviews/struck-by-lightning/2006/08/09/1154802931951.html |quote= |pages= |work=Sydney Morning Herald |location= |date=9 August 2006  |accessdate=2015-03-07 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |author=David Messer  |title=How drugs help some musicians to make music |url=http://www.smh.com.au/entertainment/music/how-drugs-help-some-musicians-to-make-music-20140811-102n4n.html |quote= |pages= |work=Sydney Morning Herald |location= |date=15 August 2014  |accessdate=2015-03-07 }}</ref>

